The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 ABB India has registered a 35 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 117.7 crore for the first quarter ended March 31, 2008. The companys revenues during the quarter rose 17 per cent to Rs 1,553.8 crore because of conversion of order backlog and consistent order intake. ABBs order book position grew 35 per cent to Rs 2 ,695.4 crore during the period. The company has also strengthened its order backlog to Rs 6,174.9 crore compared with Rs 5,026 crore at the beginning of the year. ABB has upgraded its production and testing facilities to manufacture 765KV power transformers.                             
	 Monnet Ispat and Energy Ltd has reported net sales of Rs 380.64 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2008 compared with Rs 186.45 crores in the corresponding quarter of the last fiscal, an increase of 104 per cent. Monnet recorded a 34 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 57.20 crore during the quarter against Rs 42.79 crore in the year-ago period.                            
	 Titan Industries has recorded a 42.3 per cent growth in sales income at Rs 3,041 crore for the year ended 2007-08 against Rs 2,136 crore in the previous fiscal. Profit before tax rose 53.7 per cent to Rs 202.30 crore from Rs 131.65 crore a year ago. Net profit for the year stood at Rs 150.27 crore compared with Rs 94.13 crore in the previous year.                            
	 Rallis India has registered a 115 per cent jump in profit after tax at Rs 125.19 crore for 2007-08. Profit before tax increased to Rs 146.17 crore, up 166 per cent, over Rs 55.01 crore in the previous fiscal.                             
	 Quatrro BPO Solutions has acquired Chicago-based RSM McGladrey Financial Process Outsourcing with financial participation from Sri Lankas John Keells Holdings. With this acquisition, Quatrro will add two new locations at Madison and Pleasant Prairie in Wisconsin and one in Mumbai.                             
	 Ikya Human Capital Solutions has launched interactive portal www.ikyaglobal.com. The portal has two major sections  an employment exchange for job seekers and employers and an intranet for internal consultants and associates.                            
	 Samsung has launched its 2008 series of LCD and plasma televisions. The series 6 of LCD televisions have been launched in 32, 40, 46 and 52 inch screen sizes and is priced in the range of Rs 74, 000 and Rs 3, 00,000.                            
	 Tommy Hilfiger has launched the spring summer collection of watches priced in the range of Rs 6,000-7,000. The new collection will be available at select World of Titan, Tommy Hilfiger flagship stores, Shoppers Stop, Lifestyle, Central Just in Vogue, Zimson and other multi-brand outlets.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
